Package edu.uiowa.cs.warp

Class VisualizationImplementation

java.lang.Object
edu.uiowa.cs.warp.VisualizationImplementation
All Implemented Interfaces:
edu.uiowa.cs.warp.Visualization
public class VisualizationImplementation extends Object implements edu.uiowa.cs.warp.Visualization
Creates a VisualizationImplementation that implements Visualization
Has two constructors for either a workload or warp input
Also has a default initalizer for a visualization for any object
Has different methods for ways to display the contents of the visualization: file, display, string
Has a method that creates a visualization based on a systems choice
Has a method that creates a filename template
Version:
1.5
, 1.5.1 - Maria Gauna- added JavaDoc Comments 09/21/24
Author:
sgoddard

    • VisualizationImplementation

      public VisualizationImplementation(edu.uiowa.cs.warp.WarpInterface warp, String outputDirectory, edu.uiowa.cs.warp.Visualization.SystemChoices choice)
      Constructor that creates a VisualizationImplementataion that:
      Creates a new file manager.
      Assigns the inputed warp to warp instance variable.
      Gets the fileName from the warp and assigns it the inputFileName instance variable.
      Creates a file name template based on the inputed output directory, and assigns it to the fileNameTemplete instance variable.
      Sets the visualization object equal to null and calls method createVisualization with an parameter choice sent to the constructor.
      Parameters:
      warp - an interface that gives access to methods for managing warp operations
      outputDirectory - a string that provides reference to the output directory
      choice - what is sent to the createVizualization method
      See Also:
      • method createVisualization(SystemChoices)

    • createVisualization

      private void createVisualization(edu.uiowa.cs.warp.Visualization.SystemChoices choice)
      Creates a visualization based on a choice parameter.
      A switch statement evaluates the choice, options for choices include:
      source, reliability, simulator, latency, channel, latency report, and deadline report
      The default case creates a placeholder visualization.
      Parameters:
      choice - , the type of system visualization to create

    • createVisualization

      private void createVisualization(edu.uiowa.cs.warp.Visualization.WorkLoadChoices choice)
      Creates a visualization based on a choice parameter.
      A switch statement evaluates the choice, options for choices include:
      communication graph, graph visualization, or input graph.
      The default case creates a placeholder visualization.
      Parameters:
      choice - , the type of workload visualization to make.

    • createVisualization

      private <T extends edu.uiowa.cs.warp.VisualizationObject> void createVisualization(T obj)
      Create a visualization based on an object that extends VisualizationObject that is sent as a parameter.
      Assigns the instance variable visualization equal to the object's visualization.
      Assigns the instance variable fileContent equal to the object's visualization file's content.
      Creates a file for object based on the fileNameTemplete and assigns it to the instance variable fileName.
      Sets the Visualization object equal to the obj parameter.
      Type Parameters:
      T - , a placeholder that can be filled by any object type sent as parameter.
      Parameters:
      obj - , the object that needs to be visualized.

    • createFileNameTemplate

      private String createFileNameTemplate(String outputDirectory)
      Creates a template for the file name of an outputDirectory parameter.
      Uses a file manager to make a new directory for the filename based a base directory and output directory.
      Creates the fileNameTemplate using full output path and input filename.
      Parameters:
      outputDirectory - the directory where the file will be saved.
      Returns:
      the fileNameTemplete as a string
